# Expense Tracker (Python)

## Overview

Expense Tracker is a simple Python-based console application that helps users manage their daily expenses.
Users can add expenses, view all recorded expenses, calculate the total expenditure, and delete expenses by category.
All expense data is stored in a text file (`Expense.txt`) for persistent storage.

## Features

* Add new expenses with category and amount.
* View all saved expenses.
* Calculate total expenses.
* Delete expenses by category.
* Store expense records in a text file.
* User-friendly menu-driven interface.

## Technologies Used

* Python
* File Handling
* Loops and Conditional Statements
* Exception Handling

## Project Structure

```text
Expense Tracker/
│
├── main.py
├── Expense.txt
└── README.md
```

## Future Improvements

